title: Sorry Pedro
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2QDgiyJ

by PinkEasterEggs

“I’m worried kid, why you up at 2am?”

Peter shrugged, something akin to shame filling him.

“Peter,” Mr Stark warned.

“I had a nightmare,” the boy whispered as he shuffled uncomfortably under the blankets. He wondered if Mr Stark would scoff and kick him out, telling the teen that he was too old to be suffering from nightmares.

But Mr Stark didn’t do any of what Peter feared. Instead, he stretched out a hand and ran his fingers through Peter’s curls, teasing the strands and undoing the knots. “You want to talk about it?”

Peter has a nightmare about Homecoming and Tony is there to help him through it.

summary: Art Prompts #3 @song-of-freedom is evil and asks for the hardest shit to draw while also compromising my search history!...
caption:
Art Prompts #3

@song-of-freedom is evil and asks for the hardest shit to draw while also compromising my search history! 🤣🤣🤣That’s ok, I wanted a challenge and she delivered.

#1 - Tony, Morgan, and Peter enjoying cheeseburgers

#2 - Tony and Stephen as groomsmen at their wedding

#3 - Hot IronStrange kiss.

I really like how #1 and #3 turned out but I really don’t like #2. Just… their clothes look way too silly. I don’t know, I’m terrible with clothes.

(follow the cut for ramblings and rantings)

Besides, I posted this to twitter and then RIGHT AFTER I did that, someone posted an mcu wedding fanart that looked miles better. I know we’re not supposed to compare ourselves with other people’s art, and just because one is good it doesn’t mean the other’s bad, and everything, but seeing them side by side was like… “Wow. I’m terrible at this.” 😅

I mean, this is fine. It was just the timing of it that felt like karma hitting me right across the face.

Anyway, sorry for the rambling rant. I kept it under a cut so you can just ignore it, but I had to vent my frustrations. It helped. I don’t hate it quite as much now. lol

Grace, 18, American, queer af

I ship almost everything, no hate allowed.

If you want me to tag something ask nicely and ofc I will.

Requests and prompts are always open!

summary: I know my prompts are very specific but I love the way you write my ideas lol, so here’s anotha one if you like it:   Peter used...
question: I know my prompts are very specific but I love the way you write my ideas lol, so here’s anotha one if you like it:   Peter used to be Tony’s sugar baby. It wasn’t a romantic relationship but Pete fell in love anyway. One day he catches Tony fucking another boy so he gets heartbroken and disappears from Tony’s life.  Some years later, Tony bumps into him and is shocked: Peter is now a successful businessman, ceo of his own company in England.   It could have some smut 😋 thank you 💕
answer:
Non powers- AU. Peter is 22, last month of college when it starts. Thank you for the prompt lovely

~

This was never a part of their deal. He knows it wasn’t. He knows that the fact Peter loves Tony has no effect on Tony at all. Tony doesn’t even know. At least, Peter never told him.

There’s nothing in their contract that says Tony has to only use Peter’s services. He can be with anyone he wants.

So it shouldn’t shock Peter to walk into his sugar daddy’s house and see him fucking another boy into the wall.

This boy looks nothing like Peter. He looks older, for one thing. Blonde hair, dirty blonde. Blue eyes, that are currently staring at Peter in horror. And big, rough hands that are patting Tony’s shoulder to get him to stop.

Tony does stop and look at Peter, then curses. “Shit, I didn’t know you were coming by today baby. Sorry, I’ll take this to the bedroom, my wallet is on the counter. Go have fun.” He carries the other boy to the bedroom, and the door slams behind him.

Standing in Tony’s living room, with nothing but the sounds of Tony fucking the mystery boy in the bedroom, Peter feels tears cascade down his face.

Peter works fast as soon as he makes up His mind.

He takes his key out of his pocket and lays it next to his phone. He leaves a not open on the screen.

I’m sorry I broke our contract. It’s all my fault, you didn’t do anything wrong. Here’s the key to my apartment, you own everything that’s in it, so just take it. Sorry I have to take the clothes on my back, but I’m leaving everything else. Thank you for these last few years. I’m sorry I wasn’t good enough.

-Peter

~

Peter used the money in his bank account to make his way to England. In his mind, he warned that money. He worked for it. The rest was gifts, but this he earned.

It’s enough to make a down payment on a house. Enough to buy a new wardrobe that doesn’t smell like Tony. Enough to finish his degree in business. Enough for a new phone and a new number.

It’s not enough to forget Tony Stark, but it’s enough to start.

~

Five years go by, and Tony hasn’t forgotten Peter Parker. He hadn’t forgotten how he walked out of Tony’s life, like Tony meant nothing. He hasn’t forgotten the boy that ruined Tony’s life, by walking in with a loud mouth and wild hands and ocean blue eyes that burned with fire of passion.

After he had found Peter’s phone and note, he kicked the kid out, wished him the best of luck and gave him $10,000 for staying away from him. He spent an entire year searching the entire country for Peter.

He gave up after a year, and threw himself into his work.

Now he’s at a party, talking to a bunch of CEOs from various companies. He isn’t technically supposed to be here, but he had nothing else to do, and he hates having nothing to do.

And then he sees him.

Peter is in the center of the room, laughing at some CEO’s joke, and sipping from his flute.

Tony feels like he’s died and gone to heaven. Or dreaming. He walks over to Peter, eyes wide and unseeing of anything but his boy.

“Peter?” He whispers once he’s close enough.

Peter turns and his smile fades immediately. “M-Mr. Stark. What are you doing here?” This is a party for upcoming business owners to rub elbows.

“I came to… to buy stocks in upcoming businesses… I… What are you doing here?”

Peter walks with Tony away from his group. “I own a business in England now. I started it from scratch, none of your money. All my money. I- I-“

Tony can’t help it. He touches Peter’s cheek, fingers skimming over the cheekbone. “I’ve missed you so much.” He whispers.

Peter looks down, cheeks flushing. Five years and he still hasn’t gotten over Tony Stark. “I’m sorry. I couldn’t stay. I’m sorry.”

Tony swallows thickly. “Why?” He asks the only question he’s been thinking about for five years.

Peter looks away. “I broke the contract. I fell in love with you.”

Tony’s breath hitches, and he cups Peter’s face. He kisses him softly, closing his eyes. “I love you, I haven’t stopped thinking about you this entire time, I looked everywhere for you—England—you started a business—fuck, please be with me. Please, not as a sugar baby. Be my boyfriend- please please?”

Peter pulls away, blushing. “R-really?” He asks.

Tony nods. “Really. Please?”

Peter hugs Tony, petting his hair. “I love you. I never stopped. I- yeah, I- yeah I will.”

description:
by Lurafita

Know that thing in fanfics when Peter joins the Avengers and they train him and all the people who are actually way weaker than Peter wipe the floor with him?
Because they have so much more EXPERIENCE?
Because apparently being able to bench over 10 tons and dodge bulletfire and walk away from having a building dropped on you and fighting multiple other baddies almost every day just PALES in the face of the superior EXPERIENCE!
Yeah, this is not one of those fics.

title: Star-crossed.
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2ENgG90

by songofvelius

He had accepted that death so quickly, accepted that his world will be sepia, earth and the occasional blue all over again with no same shade of vivid red to grace the canvases he paints in ridiculous pining. Sometimes it takes a little more than apologies to make good of what could and should be, but with help and introspection, Steve strives to do better for and with Tony. It’ll start with himself.
